      },
      "date": "2013-05-24 18:46:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm not a big fan of basing this check on the RHEL release version, since the kernel version may be changed if the kernel is pathed and rebuilt.  Is there a specific feature that could be checked in a header that could be used to decide if this is needed?\n\nI don't want to give this patch a -1 just for that, since it may be that this is the only way to check, but it seems like it would not be a very good long-term solution and we may have to fix it up again in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
