    {
      "id": "05b711b3f466ff587e2c06098bdb8155c88df8de",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-05-25 15:56:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (3 inline comments)\n\nI won't -1 yet, but I think future maintainability is at least worth discussing and/or exploring.\n\nI can almost guarantee that having a hard coded kernel version where it is in this patch is going to lead to future kernel updates requiring the developer to iterate over discovering why the update is failing because somebody forgot, or didn't even realize that there is a hard-coded kernel version in here.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "49a086e2433d77db1ec1fac06283619156f2a3e6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 164,
        "name": "Shuichi Ihara",
        "email": "sihara@ddn.com",
        "username": "ihara"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-25 17:00:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (3 inline comments)\n\nI agreed avoiding hardcoded kernel version in the build script, but I have no idea what OFED change the next.\n\nBTW, Mellanox new OFED 2.0 which is also based OFED-3.x, but they have another macro name to build it against RHEL6.4 kernel. The idea is same with OFED-3.5.1 (a macro to ignore kernel defined macro), but different macro name. sigh....",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
